Noella Moon, Hotel '18, shares her love for Cornell today. "Cornell is unlike any other university. It truly is a place where any person can find any study. I have been passionate about hospitality and service my entire life and I am so fortunate that Cornell has such a diverse range of studies. There is no other place in the world where I have the opportunity to gain leadership experience as a manager in a four diamond hotel, in the same building where I take all of my classes, all before I even graduate. I am so thankful to Cornell for these incredible opportunities giving me the best years of my life."

Get excited! In anticipation of Regular Decision admissions, several students will share their favorite aspects of @cornelluniversity during the next several weeks. We begin with senior Caroline Browne '17, Government and Art History. "There's nothing better than autumn in Ithaca - apple picking at Cornell Orchards, homecoming, and the Jack-o-Lantern face on the clock tower on Halloween are just a few of my favorite memories. I'm going to miss this place a lot after graduation, but I know it's a place I'll always be able to call home." We can't wait to welcome the Class of 2021 to your new home and see what you think of autumn at Cornell! Photos taken by Katie Roscoe '19 at Sapsucker Woods and Beebe Lake.
